==Esperanto==

===Etymology===
Inclusive pronouns from English ([[each]]) and French (''[[chaque]]'')

===Affix===
[[Category:Esperanto prefixes]]
'''ĉi-'''
# each-, every-, all-. (Inclusive correlative prefix.)

===Derived terms===
* ''[[ĉiu]]'': '''every''' individual, [[everyone]]
* ''[[ĉio]]'': '''every''' [object], [[everything]]
* ''[[ĉia]]'': '''every''' kind of
* ''[[ĉies]]'': belonging to '''everyone''', everyone's
* ''[[ĉiel]]'': '''every''' manner/degree
* ''[[ĉie]]'': '''every''' place, [[everywhere]]
* ''[[ĉiam]]'': '''every''' time, [[always]], [[forever]]
* ''[[ĉiom]]'': '''every''' quantity
* ''[[ĉial]]'': '''every''' reason